Defendant Auturey Ann McAdory in court.  Attorney Joel Alan Mogren Aty in court for Auturey Ann McAdory.  Prosecuting attorney Michelle A. Grasso in court for the State of Wisconsin. 
Case in court for a Return on Doctor's Report.  State and Defense have received and reviewed the Report.  The report indicates the doctor can't come to conclusion and is requesting an inpatient evaluation at a State Mental Facility.  Court ordered defendant REMANDED into the custody of the Milwaukee County Sheriff's Department to be transported FORTHWITH to a State mental health facility for a competency evaluation.

Defendant Auturey Ann McAdory in court with Attorney Joel Alan Mogren.  Jacob A. Maule appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
Case in court for status conference.  Court is advised by the defense there is reason to believe the defendant is not competent to proceed.  Pursuant to Sec. 971.14 (2) Wisconsin Statutes, Court found probable cause, temporarily stayed the proceedings, and ordered the defendant examined by the Wisconsin Forensic Unit. Order for Examination, signed and filed. Forensic evaluation will take place the Wisconsin Forensic Unit, Room 504 of the Safety Building with Dr. Niess on August 2, 2022 at 9:00 am.  Court ordered case is adjourned for Return of Doctor's Report in Branch 10.  Doctor's Report Return scheduled for August 11, 2022 at 08:30 am.
